== Procedure ==

=== Before Use ===
# Confirm the hood has a current inspection sticker.
# Verify airflow by checking the face velocity monitor or holding a tissue at the sash edge to observe inward airflow.
# Ensure the sash moves freely and the sash stop is set at the correct height.
# Remove any unnecessary materials from the hood — keep the work area uncluttered.

=== During Use ===
# Keep the sash at or below the safe operating height at all times.
# Work at least 6 inches (15 cm) back from the sash opening.
# Do not place your head inside the hood.
# Keep large equipment toward the back of the hood to avoid disrupting airflow.
# Elevate large items on blocks to allow airflow underneath.
# Avoid rapid movements near the hood face — they create turbulence that can pull vapors out.

=== After Use ===
# Remove all chemicals and materials, or move them to the back of the hood.
# Lower the sash to the fully closed position when the hood is not in use.
# Wipe down the work surface with appropriate cleaning solution.
# Dispose of waste according to EHS guidelines.

== Maintenance and Inspection ==
* Fume hoods are inspected annually by EHS. Do not use a hood with an expired inspection sticker.
* Report any unusual noise, reduced airflow, or alarm conditions to facilities management immediately.
* Do not attempt to repair or modify the hood yourself.
